modules.description: Provides functions to load and apply video filters from the frei0r library, including filter creation, parameter setting, and rendering. Works with pixel data, filter parameters, and video frames represented as arrays. Used to implement real-time video effects in multimedia applications.

This module enables plugin management and data manipulation through functions for retrieving metadata like version and parameter types, along with in-place array updates using structured data such as color and position values. It supports graphics/image processing workflows by handling custom plugin states and parameter adjustments, including boolean, float, and string values. Specific use cases involve real-time effect rendering and parameter-driven transformations in multimedia applications.
